description.narrative: With the advocacy work, UNICEF has contributed to support the increase of budget allocations to social sectors in the Supplementary Budget 2019/20 ($176m); and called for a renewed, people-centered approach to planning and budgeting, towards investing in human capital. The increasing support provided by PF4C to other programmes – education, nutrition, health – has strengthened the public policies/finance component and the equity angle. Key results in 2020 include the roll-out of the Health Micro-Insurance in Myanmar and the agreement on the Child Friendly Cities and Communities Initiatives (CFCI) Concept Note with Yangon City Development Committee (YCDC). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/07/2020
